INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'c956ad10-31d8-49ec-adf2-eb021518170f',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Cassandra Security — Encryption, RBAC, and Least Privilege Done Right$escape$,
  $escape$Cassandra's security model has three independent layers you must configure explicitly — none are on by default.

For encryption in transit, set `client_encryption_options` and `server_encryption_options` in `cassandra.yaml`, pointing to your keystore/truststore. Internode encryption (`server_encryption_options: internode_encryption: all`) is often skipped and leaves your cluster gossip exposed.

For encryption at rest, Cassandra relies on the JVM's `javax.crypto` via a `system_key` file or an external KMS integration (DataStax Enterprise adds transparent encryption; OSS requires filesystem-level encryption like LUKS or cloud-provider disk encryption).

For access control, flip `authenticator: PasswordAuthenticator` and `authorizer: CassandraAuthorizer` in `cassandra.yaml`, then restart. From there, use CQL roles with scoped GRANT statements. Avoid the `cassandra` superuser in production — create a dedicated admin role and rotate the default credentials immediately.

Cassandra has no native row-level security. Enforce data isolation at the keyspace or table level using role grants, and push row-filtering logic to the application layer.$escape$,
  $escape$-- Enable auth in cassandra.yaml first, then:
CREATE ROLE app_reader WITH PASSWORD = 'str0ng!' AND LOGIN = TRUE;
CREATE ROLE app_writer WITH PASSWORD = 'wr1te!' AND LOGIN = TRUE;

-- Least privilege: reader gets SELECT only on one table
GRANT SELECT ON TABLE analytics.events TO app_reader;

-- Writer gets DML but NOT DDL
GRANT MODIFY ON TABLE analytics.events TO app_writer;
GRANT SELECT ON TABLE analytics.events TO app_writer;

-- Revoke all rights from the default superuser in prod
ALTER ROLE cassandra WITH PASSWORD = 'rotated-and-vaulted' AND SUPERUSER = FALSE;$escape$,
  $escape$sql$escape$,
