INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '3582a2e5-0799-4e07-a012-c3428382bd4f',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Cassandra Zero-Downtime Migrations — Additive-Only DDL and Schema Agreement$escape$,
  $escape$Cassandra propagates DDL via gossip, not a centralized coordinator — schema state can temporarily diverge across nodes. For zero-downtime migrations, only additive changes are safe during rolling deploys: `ALTER TABLE ... ADD` is non-blocking, but `DROP COLUMN` leaves tombstone metadata for the full `gc_grace_seconds` window, and renaming non-primary-key columns isn't supported at all.

To change a column's type safely, use the dual-write pattern: add the new column, deploy code that writes to both, backfill historical rows via DSBulk or a Spark job, cut reads to the new column, then defer `DROP` until all nodes have compacted past `gc_grace_seconds`.

Before any DDL, verify cluster-wide schema agreement — `nodetool describecluster` reports `Schema versions`. More than one UUID means a node is lagging; applying further DDL during disagreement risks split-brain schema state that requires manual `nodetool resetlocalschema` to recover.

For version-controlled migrations, `cassandra-migrate` tracks applied CQL scripts with SHA checksums and exposes a `status` command to detect drift. Pair it with a pre-migration check against a local CCM cluster in CI to catch CQL syntax errors before they hit production.$escape$,
  $escape$-- 1. Verify schema agreement before any DDL
--    nodetool describecluster | grep 'Schema versions'
--    Must show exactly ONE UUID. If two appear, wait for gossip convergence.

-- 2. Safe additive migration (non-blocking, gossip-propagated)
ALTER TABLE user_events ADD metadata map<text, text>;

-- 3. Dual-write pattern: introduce new column alongside old
ALTER TABLE user_events ADD event_source_v2 varchar;

-- 4. After DSBulk backfill + full app cutover to event_source_v2:
--    Wait gc_grace_seconds (default 864000s / 10 days), then:
ALTER TABLE user_events DROP event_source;$escape$,
